 Debugging and Logging in Spark
Understanding how to debug and log can help diagnose issues.

Step 1: Set Log Level
Scala:

scala
 
scala> sc.setLogLevel("ERROR")
Python:

 
 
>>> sc.setLogLevel("ERROR")
Step 2: Use explain() to Understand Query Plan
Scala:

scala
 
scala> df.explain()
Python:

 
 
>>> df.explain()
Step 3: Check Spark Web UI
While your application is running, access the Web UI at http://localhost:4040 to view detailed information about jobs and stages.
